 <caption>An isobaric expansion of a gas requires heat transfer to keep the pressure constant. Since pressure is constant, the work done is <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi fontstyle="italic">P</m:mi><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{PΔV} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</caption></figure><para id="eip-69">Recall from mechanics that work done by a force <m:math><m:ci>F</m:ci></m:math> on an object undergoing displacement <m:math><m:ci>d</m:ci></m:math> is</para><equation id="fs-id1169736619217"><m:math>
