   </m:math>  (isobaric process). There are some—especially chemists—who use this definition of work, and not the definition based on internal pressure, as the basis of the First Law of Thermodynamics.  This definition reverses the sign conventions for work, and results in a statement of the first law that becomes  <m:math>
